The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Eveready sales rise 13% 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Eveready sales rise 13% 
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, April 30: City-based Eveready Industries has reported a 13 per cent growth in net sales at Rs 968.73 crore during 2009-10 against Rs 857.33 crore in the previous fiscal.         
	Net income grew to Rs 227.41 crore from Rs 204.20 crore last year.         
	Profit before depreciation, interest and tax stood at Rs 23.64 crore against Rs 18.59 crore a year ago.         
	During 2009-10, the company has posted a 633 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 142.21 crore compared with Rs 19.40 crore in the year-ago period.         
	The company targets a topline growth of 20 per cent during 2010-11.        
	It has also increased the prices of batteries, flashlights and lighting products, passing on the hike in excise duty to consumers. The price hikes ranged between 4 per cent and 7 per cent.        
	The company had recently said it expected its turnover to increase to Rs 2,000 crore over the next three years on the back of volume sales and acquisitions in the domestic FMCG space.        
	In May last year, Eveready had picked up an 80 per cent stake in France-based Uniross SA for 10 million euros.         
	The company has entered into an agreement with Paris-based CG Holding, which holds around 70 per cent in Uniross, to secure the deal.                    
	Eveready has sold its land in Mumbai whose the entry has now being concluded of Rs 106 crore, which is accounted in this quarter.                                                                                                                                      
